The Chronicle Innocent Kurira, Sports Reporter
THE clash between Zifa Southern Region Division One log leaders Hwange and third-placed Arenel will headline resumption of league action following a mid-season break. Arenel are nine points behind Hwange, who sit on 45 points. Hwange edged Arenel 1-0 in the reverse fixture before the break in what had been dubbed as the title decider. <img class="wp-image-618778 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-35-9.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-35-9.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-35-9-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Adonice Nyoni Hwangeâ€™s goal was scored in the 42nd minute via the penalty spot by captain Kelly Shiyandindi.Arenel were unhappy with the awarding of the penalty and their technical team is reported to have confronted referee Donacious Munenge at full-time in protest. Arenel will be hoping to collect maximum points to remain in the title race against their biggest rivals. Meanwhile, Quality Foods striker Stanson Khanye is the leading goal scorer in the league at the halfway stage. <img class="wp-image-618769 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/stanson.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/stanson.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/stanson-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Stanson Khanye  Khanye has found the target 11 times followed by Shiyandindi and Ryan Ncube of Mosi Rovers, who are tied on eight goals, with Tinotenda Chitete of Makhandeni Pirates on seven. Shepherd Gadzikwa (Hwange), Adonice Nyoni (Arenel), Aluma Milanzi (Binga Pirates), Fortune Nkomazana (ZPC Hwange), Tendai Zaza (Mountain Climbers) and Calvin Chigonera (Talen Vision) have each scored six goals.  Fixtures Today
Main Line vs ZPC Hwange (Plumtree, 3pm), Zimbabwe Saints vs Bosso 90 (Luveve B Arena, 3pm), Casmyn vs Mountain Climbers (Turk Mine, 3pm), Ratanang vs Mosi Rovers (Luveve 3pm), CIWU vs Indlovu Iyanyathela (Luveve, 12pm), Talen Vision vs Makhandeni Pirates (Filabusi, 3pm), Arenel Movers vs Hwange (White City, 12pm), Binga Pirates vs Ajax Hotspurs (Binga, 3pm), Indonsakusa vs Quality Foods (White City, 3pm).